From: jaewun <jaewun@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] scsi: ufs: qcom: propagate hibern8 exit failure from clk_scale_notify

ufs_qcom_clk_scale_notify() wakes the link with ufshcd_uic_hibern8_exit()
after a POST_CHANGE clock scale but drops its return value and always returns 0.
Every other error in this function (hibern8 enter, the pre/post change helpers)
is captured and returned; only this success-path link-wake was silently ignored.

If the link fails to exit hibern8 -- e.g. a marginal M-PHY after a deep-suspend
PHY collapse -- the function reports success to the clock-scaling core. The core
(ufshcd_scale_clks) is built to consume a non-zero POST_CHANGE return: on failure
it rolls back the OPP/clock frequency, leaves target_freq unchanged, and the
devfreq governor logs the failure and retries on the next poll. Returning 0
defeats all of that and records a stale frequency on a link that never woke.

Capture and return the error so the failure is honestly propagated to the
clock-scaling/devfreq accounting and rollback path instead of being masked as
success. Note: link recovery itself is NOT triggered by this return -- the
failing UIC command already schedules the error handler from inside
ufshcd_uic_pwr_ctrl() (link-broken + schedule_eh_work) before the return
propagates. This patch only stops the false-success accounting.

An equivalent fix was proposed upstream but not merged; mainline still carries
this bug.

Signed-off-by: jaewun <jaewun@users.noreply.github.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-qcom.c b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-qcom.c
--- a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-qcom.c
@@ -1779,8 +1779,8 @@
 		}

 		ufs_qcom_icc_update_bw(host);
-		ufshcd_uic_hibern8_exit(hba);
+		err = ufshcd_uic_hibern8_exit(hba);
 	}

-	return 0;
+	return err;
 }
